# Core Systems Rules (Autoloads)

These files are global singletons loaded for the entire game session.

## Requirements
- Every public function must have a return type annotation
- Every signal must have typed parameters
- No direct scene manipulation — core scripts must be scene-agnostic
- Use `clampi`/`clampf` for bounded values, never raw arithmetic
- Dictionary values from user data must be explicitly typed (no `:=` with Variant)
- Save/load: every new persistent field must be added to `get_save_data()` AND `load_save_data()`
- Constants use SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE
- Enums at the top of the file, after signals

## Performance
- No allocations in functions called every frame
- Prefer `match` over chained `if/elif` for string/enum dispatch
- Signals over polling — never check state in `_process()` when a signal exists
